article.headline: UNLV 75, Utah 65
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- TreVon Willis scored a career-high 22 points to lead UNLV over Utah 75-65 Saturday. Wink Adams and Rene Rougeau added 14 points each for the Runnin' Rebels (16-4, 4-2 Mountain West). Adams had 12 points in the second half, when the Rebels rallied after trailing 38-30 at halftime. Luke Nevill led Utah (12-7, 3-2) with 14 points and seven rebounds. Shaun Green, Luka Drca, and Lawrence Borha added 11 points apiece for the Utes, who hit 10 3-pointers. The Rebels outscored the Utes 45-27 in the second half.
